<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Interesting post.<P>I've found that the best groups aren't made up of particular classes, but particular people.  Good players can make or break a group much faster than good classes.<P>Diversity is good.  From heavy melee "pull, park and whack" groups to heavy caster "nuke, kite and med" groups to balanced groups, the people make it work or make it fail.<P>I do think that bards and/or enchanters are just downright useful for my groups.  With high damage output groups, a shaman or druid does just as well as a cleric.  Warrior, monks, rangers, paladins and rogues all can make nifty tanks.<P>A good puller is important for high XP groups.  They need to know the area, the mobs and the capabilities of the rest of the group.<P>Casters need to know aggro and mana management.<P>Tanks need to be pro-active.<P>Everyone needs to be on the ball.<P>pax,<BR>-Xoxxala<P>--------------------<P>Xoxxala Oxxoxxulous - Wizard of E'ci
</FONT>
