<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I think category 9 could be "wipeout prevention/recovery" It seems that most groups deal with a bad overpull by having the cleric camp out and everyone else dying. Once the mobs wander off, the cleric logs back in and resurrects everyone. If it works, it's much more time efficient than having everyone walk back from the evac point, even counting the time spent recovering the 6% exp lost.<P>Sad, but true. Of course, if you don't have a cleric handy, getting the evac is better then spending hours trying to get a cleric.
</FONT>
