To Simryd <P>Ok first off I am happy to see some one giving reasons why they think wizards are ballanced that goes beyond " I like playing my wiz and can alway get in a group so they must be ballanced "  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"> . However, I would have to disagree with you list of main group requirements.<P>1. Taunting (also involves Damage Absorbtion)<BR>2. Pulling<BR>3. Damage Dealing<BR>4. Primary Healing<BR>5. Mesmerisation<BR>6. Snaring<BR>7. Spell interruption (via Stuns and/or BASH)<BR>8. Rooting<BR>9. Evacuation<P>From my experiance only 1,2,3,4,5 & 6 are actually valuable to the average group. Items 7, 8 & 9 are situational at best just like lock picking and traking, SOW is much more valuable than any of these skills ( and even though it can only be used outside it is needed much more offten than items 7,8 & 9). Further more you forgot to add mana regeneration ( this is one of the most valuable skills to a group in the game ), Stat buffing, haste, and mob debuffing to your list ( all of which are vary valuable to groups much more so than items 7, 8, & 9). That means wizards only fullfill items 3 & 6 and they are sub par at both. <P>As for the mag, well when they cant use there pet I would agree they are in even worse shape than a wizard but when they can use there pet they will be at least twice as valuable as a wizard.<P>With this in mind your break down would look more like this : ( I have put *'s next to the skills that are the top 4 that groups look for, removed items 7,8,&9,  and added the items you left out ).<P>Other skills you left out.<P>10 mana regeneration<BR>11 Stat buffing<BR>12 haste<BR>13 mob debuffing<P>Warrior: 1*,2,3*,(6 with Kunzar Ku'jusch)<BR>Monk: 2,3*<BR>Rogue: 2,3*,(6 with SBD)<P>Paladin: 1*,2,3*<BR>Shadow Knight: 1*,2,3*,6<BR>Ranger: 1*,2,3*,6<BR>Bard: 3*,5,6, 10*, 11<P>Cleric: 3*,4*,(6 with Regent Symbol of Innoruuk), 11<BR>Shaman: 3*,4*,11,12,13(?? Im not sure about this one for the shamen)<BR>Druid: 3*,4*,6,11,12<P>Enchanter: 3*(?? since when do enchanter deal any real damage ),5, 10*,11,12,13<BR>Wizard: 3*,6<BR>Magician: 3*,13<BR>Necromancer: 3*,5,6,13<P>In this case wizards arent looking so good  <IMG SRC="frown.gif" border="0"> <P>Also you cant just say that class A gets this ability and there for adds to a group regardless of how well they perform that task. A wizard get a 5dmg damage shield that lasts 2 min, does that meen that it is even half as good as a 35dmg damage shild that last 10 min, or a 20dmg DS that can be cast on the whole group at once and last 8 min. Look at the druids, before the last upgrade they were worthless as a healers post 50.<P>It seems like you are looking for some way to show wizards are ballanced, and at least your are providing some real reasons for your beliefs  <IMG SRC="wink.gif" border="0"> . However I would say that in actuality, there are only 5 realy valuable skills groups look for if they want to be sucessfull<P>1. Taunting<BR>2. Damage dealing<BR>3. Healing<BR>4. Mana Regenerating<BR>5. Buffing<P>In this case the break down would look something like this :<P>Warrior: 1,2<BR>Monk: 2<BR>Rogue: 2<P>Paladin: 1,2<BR>Shadow Knight: 1,2<BR>Ranger: 1,2<BR>Bard: 2,4,5<P>Cleric: 3,5<BR>Shaman: 3,5<BR>Druid: 3,5<P>Enchanter: 4,5<BR>Wizard: 2<BR>Magician: 2<BR>Necromancer: 2,4<P>Once again wiz doesnt look so good especialy when you consider there damage limitations  <IMG SRC="frown.gif" border="0">
