Once again, the true test is to do a fight with a WIzard and replace him with, oh, a Warrior.  See if you suffer any as a result, or if you are the same or better.  The best group I was ever in was 4 warriors, a cleric, and a Bard.  We cremated everything we faced, with almost no downtime whatsoever, and they died FAST.<P>Subjective things like "I feel useful" and "My buddies like me there" really don't prove nor disprove anything.  That's why there are numbers posted.  <P>Basically Wizards can do their job ok, but there's a problem with how easily they are replaced with the group benefitting by this transfer, and with the technical ability on paper to do more damage but the near total inability to see that happen in real life.
