<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Ok, Mandingo, I'll take you up on that....<P>Last night I was grouped with a warrior and a druid in Lower Guk, in the mushroom area.  We were fighting happily along, with me in my usual role - druid snarepulls, warrior and druid beat it down to half, I nuke once to make it a runner, warrior finishes while druid pulls next.  <BR>Things were clicking right along, when we had a room repop - two shammies who start healing the Fungus Soldier the others were beating on.  I calmly stood up - 80 mana or so - rooted a shaman, burned it down - rooted the second, resisted his Drowsy, burned him down.  Sat down to medd at 10 mana and told the others I was going to be sitting out the next fight or two.<P>Ok, Mandy, let's put a second warrior in my spot.  Warrior, warrior, druid - not a bad group at all.  But when all three are working a fighter type and two healers show up, best tactic is to go to one-on-one - and even in the low 20s it's not likely for a warrior to go toe to toe with a blue and walk away happy.  If we'd been two warriors and a druid, we might have had some serious trouble.  <BR>Yes, a warrior will outdamage me over the course of a half-hour.  But when we need something dead NOW, the wizard is the choice.<P>Rhian B'Zorch<P>P.S. Admitted, I'm slightly twinked - int is 166 and I have over 100 mana in plus gear.  So yes, I can burn down a blue and a green by myself.<BR>RBZ
