TO Simryd<P>If you enjoy playing the wizard class then it does not matter if it is broken or not. Having fun is the point of a game so dont let thoughs of us who think it is broken ruin it for you.  <IMG SRC="biggrin.gif" border="0"> <P>Regarding the importance of snare.<P>As for snaring being important, well I would agree that if you dont have and enchanter or a druid or a shamen, then having the wizards bonds of foce is nice. However I would not say it is essential or even make it into the top 10 things group look for. But that is my opinion and if you can get into group becuase you have bonds of force, I then who am I to agrue.<P>As you lvl up I think you will find that stun spells become much more valualbe than snare spells to groups, although I dont think this would make it into the top 10 things groups look for either. Unfortunatly most mobs become unstunable post lvl 40 so basicaly your stun spells become realy mana draining nuks with low damage out put.<P>Regarding wizards being good at damage dealing.<P>Well there I have to disagree and I would say that if you think they are you are deluding yourself. Yes wizards are better than any wisdom based caster or an enchanter at dooing damage but the are below everyone else ( at least were damage over time is conserved ). A wizard can do fast damage ( faster than any other class for that maner ) however the higher lvl you get the less important fast damage becomes ( also tanks can do damage so fast that if you only nuke once the time differance is so inconsiquestial that if they had another tank instead of the wiz the fight time would actuall by shorter ).<P>But once again if you are having fun playing your wiz, who cares of the class is ballanced or broken. Have fun and dont worry about it. But if you stop having fun dont keep playing the wiz hoping it will get better, becuase it only gets worse. Trust once the wizard stops being fun, you are much better off just retiring him than trying to get him to lvl 60 ( that will just make you a bitter hatefull wiz like me LOL  <IMG SRC="biggrin.gif" border="0"> )
