<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
It's really a game of semantics. Broken. Unbalanced. What's the difference?  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><P>The wizard class is clearly not broken, because it is the 5-th most sought-after class for raids (behind Warriors, Rogues, Clerics, and Enchanters... if you don't believe me here, ask some high level folks). It is not broken, because the more you have, the better (unlike shamans slowing, necros DoTs, Mage/Druid damage shields, etc). It is not broken because it can perform several mandatory grouping tasks (SNARE, evac, damage). It is not broken because it can solo more efficiently than any other class during some level ranges (quad-kiting), assuming access to SoW potions or JBoots. It is not broken because it is fun for many to play. <P>However, if you tell me that the wizard class is unbalanced, then I wholeheartedly agree. It is unbalanced during many pre-49 level ranges. Especially from 24 to 28 and from 34 to 43. Their nukes aren't quite powerful, speedy, or efficient enough to compete with the proliferation of twinked tanks out there. Verant should have anticipated this, and should now compensate by enhancing most wizard nukes by reducing cast time, enhancing efficiency, or enhancing damage (pick 2 out of the three and I'll be satisfied). Mages are just too dang close in nuking efficiency until lv 49, so easily overcome by their pet. I still think Mages should ALWAYS outdamage wizards with their pet, but not by the enormous gap they now do pre-49.<P>Like I said earlier, I believe that if they moved Lightning Shock to lv 34, Conflag to lv 39, Rend to 44, and slightly reduced the casting times on all three of these, and maybe even reduced the mana cost a wee bit, I would be 100% happy with the class.<P>Happy hunting to you all, and I hope you have fun whatever you decide to do!  <IMG SRC="biggrin.gif" border="0">
</FONT>
