Wizards snaring???<P>Yes, if the group needs a snarer and you're the only who can then obviously you have to do it.<P>But our snare cost so much mana and has such a short duration that it negates our small edge in DD mana efficiency.  Druid Ensare has a much longer duration than bonds and only costs 35 mana.<P>If you get a pull of more than one mob you'll have to cast bonds at least twice.  By the time the first mob dies, bonds will have worn off the second mob if it didn't resist it outright.<P>Two casts of bonds = 150 mana spent.  Throw in a resist and that's 225 mana spent just to snare a couple mobs.
