<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
One question - Why does everyone attempt to differentiate the Wizard from the Warrior? The warrior is good at what he does. His job (in high level groups) is to whack the heck out of the mob and keep him off the wizard. So we can do our job. It is not surprise they would outdamage us. Then again, do you see the warrior soloing at high levels? I've never seen it done. and believe it or not? They have more downtime than we do if they decide to solo. If you are going to compare the wizard to another class - we need to compare a class in which is closer to us. <P>Lets say for instance - a warrior and a monk? in a duel (if both rather twinked to their level) the monk will win. Why? They dodge, repost, and hit faster than the warrior. If you argue this, then I don't know if you've ever played a warrior and dueled a monk.<P>This goes for the Wizard. If a wizard duels a warrior? A Wizard would win in a heart beat. Out of mana? No problem - (invisibility / medding). Nuke and die. Not hard at all. So therefore we are not useless. We are very powerful. (post lvl 49)<P>Velious resists are wonderful... ye know why? I don't think you're supposed to solo high mobs in Velious - afterall Verant created Velious, tweeked it out for the veteran players. Go figure.<P>Better luck on the new upgrade. maybe we'll get something more valuable than a O'keil's Flickering Flame...?<P>~Gideon Leviticus
</FONT>
