<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Duelling doesn't realy tell you much about the power or value of a class.  A rogue sucks in duels, they won't ever be behind any PC with the slightest level of intelligence, and as such have to rely on their lower AC and hope they can damage you faster than you do them.  Their sneak/hide isn't especially helpful, their backstab doesn't do much, and their poison isn't likely to come into play.<P>That doesn't mean rogues suck or are weak, it just means duels do not equal actual Everquest.  If a Wizard can easily flatten a Warrior over x level in a duel, that just tells me Wizards are dangerous in duels (past x level), not that they are terrific in Everquest.
</FONT>
