<BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Originally posted by <fuzzle>:<BR><B>umm.. wtf would you want mage/druid nuke efficiency increased? especially if wizards' were increased???<P>that's defeating the purpose of improving our nuke superiority<P>p.s. evacs not useful? cough</B><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Because if you're going to talk about class balance you have to talk about all classes and not just keep your blinders on thinking about your class.  Mages are damage dealers and nothing more.  Sure we can debuff a little and cast mod rods woohoo...but basically we're damage dealers, and as you get into the upper levels and the mobs keep getting higher and higher in level as compared to your pet you will find that your nukes are the only way to really deal damage as a mage (especially when people won't let you use your pet)<BR>I personally think that you should be given higher damage spells post 50.  I think a level 60 wizard should be able to nuke on certain mobs for like 5k dmg per cast.  I also think that a mage should be given better post 50 nukes.  (although they sorta did by fixing our rain spells)<BR>Remember alot of people have some of the same problems you have.  Verant might fix something if more than one class suffers from the same problems.  (i.e. putting far superior melee items in game with RoK and SoV to balance out the caster supremacy pre-expansions) <BR>Fight with us not against us man<P>--------------------<P>Tomlyn Drayke-Lvl 53 Elementalist<BR>Falkan Strydewell-Lvl 39 Paladin<BR>Fallken-Lvl 19 Rogue<BR>Sigmacrunk-Lvl 11 Iksar Shaman<BR>Prexus<P>"But whosoever should cross that line, into true corruption,into our domain....One day you will look behind you and you will see We Three, and on that day, YOU WILL REAP IT!" ---"Boondock Saints"
