<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
This thread is about "grouping essentials," and I find it strange no one has mentioned a wizards meditate style.<P>Are you the kind of wizard who meds absolutely every single second of the game that you're not nuking?  No?  You can /assist while meditating.  Why not do it?<P>I see <B>a lot</B> of wizards in groups with me who stand up to nuke, nuke, watch the pretty lights, stand around, change position, look left and right, maybe nuke again, stand around some more.  Okay!  Fight is over!  Time to loot!<BR>Uhm - hi.  That wiz just spent 30 seconds standing around.  I spent 24 of those seconds meditating.<P>No, you sure don't get any loot this way, but you sure can pile up some mana.<P>All you Pro Wizards are probably doing this already.  Sorry if I offend anyone.  I have yet to see more than 1 out of 5 wizards in-game as meditation-obsessed as I am.   <IMG SRC="tongue.gif" border="0"><P>--------------------<P>What sin has not been committed in the name of efficiency?<P>Occulis Rift <BR>Tarew Marr
